parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, especially on wet or slippery surfaces.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle does not stop or slows down insufficiently
the brakes lock up
the vehicle experiences a false sense of stopping
the ABS system fails to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat recliner can cause the seat to fall backward, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, especially in cases where the driver or passenger is not properly restrained.
symptoms: The front seat recliner falls backward
the seat back breaks off completely
the pins that hold the seat to the base shear off
the driver or passenger falls forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation on start and throughout the driving range can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Hesitation on start
hesitation throughout the driving range
difficulty starting the vehicle
the engine turns over but won't start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the steering column from the housing can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Steering column slowly unscrewing itself
loose steering wheel
difficulty steering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of the paint can lead to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Paint peeling
discoloration
paint fading from original color to grey.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ignition won't turn to off position
difficulty starting the vehicle
the engine turns over but won't start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the door handles from the inside door panel can cause difficulty entering or exiting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Door handles separated from inside door panel
difficulty opening or closing doors.
